pr_title: PR for Reviewing VisualScript Module(aka Submodules) Patch
pr_body: Preview PR to allow for an easier view over the changes required for the addition of modules(previously submodules) to Visual Script on top of the Visual Script Refactor PR.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 455927213, 'comment_body': 'Is Resource the correct type?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 16, 16, 47, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'fire', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 456743798, 'comment_body': "Resource to Script casts happening implicitly. Considering it's used as Script is there a reason to use Resource type?
", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 18, 3, 41, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'kidrigger', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 456871417, 'comment_body': "I don't think that it makes a difference, there is a is valid check just below it.... :/

If there is a place without is_valid check then yes that will be a problem. (And I do plan to fix it or move to using a base type that will not have such issues)", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 19, 7, 12, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'swarnimarun', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 456871819, 'comment_body': "As I was discussing last time, we could make a base type that allows us to do it, I could even use VisualScript itself as the base type for submodules but at the moment I am not sure because I am not sure all the features that we should add to submodules from visualscript.

- [x] Finish some leftover TODOs based on these functionality changes.
- [x] Squash commits when everything is done.
- [x] Test the code further.

cc: @fire @kidrigger
